# Bulk Edits Branch Policy

- Before starting any huge or bulk change, create a separate git branch from `master`.
- Never implement bulk edits directly on `master`.
- Use a descriptive branch name for bulk work (example: `bulk/refactor-theme-options`).
- Treat changes as bulk when they affect many files, shared architecture, or a wide refactor scope.
- If asked to start a new bulk edit while another bulk branch context exists, pause and ask:
  - "Should this new bulk branch be planned to merge into `master`, or stay isolated for now?"
- Do not begin the new bulk implementation until the user answers that merge-intent question.
- Record the user decision in the branch/PR description so merge intent stays explicit.
